{{Infobox artwork | image_file =File:Harlequin with a Guitar MET DP169316.jpg | caption = | alt = | image_size = | title =Harlequin with a Guitar | other_language_1 = | other_title_1 = | other_title_2 = | artist = [[Juan Gris]] | subject = | year = 1917 | material = Oil on wood panel | height_metric = 100.3 | width_metric = 65.1 | length_metric = | diameter_metric = | city = [[New York City]] | museum = [[Metropolitan Museum of Art]] | accession = 2008.468 }} '''''Harlequin with a Guitar''''' is an early 20th century painting by Spanish [[Cubism|cubist]] [[Juan Gris]]. Done in oil on panel, the work is in the collection of the [[Metropolitan Museum of Art]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.metmuseum.org/art/collection/search/490068| title=metmuseum.org|website=www.metmuseum.org|access-date=2018-09-13}}</ref>
The Harlequin with his checkered costume was a favorite theme of cubists and Gris himself portrayed him in approximately forty works between 1917 and 1925.
