'''Kanstantsia Builo''' ({{lang-be|Канстанцыя Буйло}}) (1893&ndash;1986) was a Belarusian poet and playwright. Her first publication was in 1909, ''Mound Flower'', which was edited by [[Yanka Kupala]]. The main themes of her poems, which often relied on folklore, was peasant life In Belarus before 1917, and World War II heroism.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://kupala-library.iatp.by/bel_lit/b.html|title=Kanstantsia Builo|publisher=The Belarusian Literature in English Translations, Yanka Kupala Central Public Library, Minsk|accessdate=8 January 2013}}</ref> One of her most notable poems was ''I Love Our Land''.

